    &lt;CommentText&gt;My Dad was first on the stroke unit in July and is now on the renal unit and I the last time I spoke to someone was 24-11-20 and I have been trying since to get through to both the ward and the main switchboard. I am so appreciative of everything that the NHS do and have been doing for my Dad, but he is 84 not seeing anyone and has now not spoken to anyone in a week and it is making him deteriorate further at a great pace. I just want an update but the phone never gets answered. Hi wife my Mum has dementia and it is also making her a lot worse. I don't know what other numbers to try an call. He is on ward 37. I know the priority is the care of patients and you have such a hard job, but it is also hard on the outside when you don't know what is going on with your loved one and haven't been able to contact anyone for a week to ask.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
